## PART 5 — CHAT INTERFACE

### 5.1 Chat Panel Layout

Right side of the screen, full height, ~380px wide.
Split: chat history (scrollable) + agent control panel + input.

```
┌────────────────────────────────┐
│  🎬 Inkframe Agent             │
├────────────────────────────────┤
│                                │
│  [chat history scrolls here]   │
│                                │
│  ┌────────────────────────┐    │
│  │ Scene Maker            │    │
│  │ ─────────────────────  │    │
│  │ Generated scene 2 with │    │
│  │ 3 layers:              │    │
│  │ • Canvas2D: background │    │
│  │ • D3: bar chart        │    │
│  │ • HTML: title + labels │    │
│  │                        │    │
│  │ [Preview updated ↗]   │    │
│  └────────────────────────┘    │
│                                │
├────────────────────────────────┤
│ ⚙ Agent Settings       [−/+]  │
│ [Agent Control Panel here]     │
├────────────────────────────────┤
│ ┌──────────────────────────┐   │
│ │ Tell me what to create...│   │
│ └──────────────────────────┘   │
│ [Send]  [Voice]  [Undo ↩]     │
└────────────────────────────────┘
```

### 5.2 Message Types

User messages: right-aligned, dark bubble.

Agent messages: left-aligned, colored border matching agent type.
Each agent message shows:
- Agent name badge (Director / Scene Maker / Editor / DoP)
- Model used badge (sonnet / haiku / local)
- The response text
- Tool calls made (collapsible): "Called add_layer × 3, set_transition × 1"
- Preview link if scene was updated: "Scene 2 updated →"

System messages (not from agent): gray, italic.
  "Switched to Editor agent"
  "Scene context set to Scene 3"
  "Three.js tool disabled"

### 5.3 Streaming

Stream Claude's response token by token into the chat bubble.
Tool calls execute server-side as they complete (not streamed).
After each tool call completes, send a SSE event:
  { type: 'tool_complete', tool: 'add_layer', sceneId, layerId }
Frontend receives this, triggers scene HTML regeneration + iframe reload.
User sees the preview updating in real time as the agent works.

### 5.4 Undo/Redo

Every tool call that modifies world state creates a snapshot before executing.
Undo button in chat input reverses the last snapshot.
Redo re-applies it.
Show in chat: "↩ Undid: add_layer (Canvas2D background) on Scene 2"
The agent can also undo: "undo" → editor agent calls undo_last_action tool.

### 5.5 Agent Visibility Into Its Own Actions

After each tool call completes, inject a brief summary
into the agent's context:
  "Tool add_layer completed. Layer id: layer-abc123.
   Scene 2 now has 3 layers: [canvas2d: bg], [d3: chart], [html: title].
   Occupied regions in scene 2: top 20% (title), center (chart)."

This lets the agent make spatially-aware decisions on subsequent calls.
Prevents it from placing elements on top of each other.

---

## PART 6 — SCENE HTML GENERATION

### 6.1 Multi-Layer HTML Template

Each scene generates a single HTML file that composites all layers:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Caveat:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <style>
    * { margin:0; padding:0; box-sizing:border-box; }
    body { width:1920px; height:1080px; overflow:hidden;
           background:{scene.bgColor}; position:relative; }
    
    .inkframe-layer {
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      width: 1920px;
      height: 1080px;
    }
    
    /* Layer-specific opacity/blend */
    {layerStyles}
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <!-- LAYER: video background (if present) -->
  {videoLayerHTML}

  <!-- LAYERS: rendered in z-order -->
  {layers.map(layer => renderLayer(layer))}

  <!-- INTERACTION OVERLAY (interactive mode only) -->
  {interactionOverlayHTML}

  <!-- SCRIPTS: load libraries, then run layer code -->
  <script src="https://unpkg.com/roughjs@4.6.6/bundled/rough.js"></script>
  <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/d3/7.9.0/d3.min.js"></script>
  <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/three.js/r128/three.min.js"></script>
  <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/bodymovin/5.12.2/lottie.min.js"></script>
  <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/animejs/3.2.2/anime.min.js"></script>

  <!-- Inlined canvas renderer utilities -->
  <script>{inlinedCanvasRenderer}</script>

  <!-- Asset library (only assets used in this scene) -->
  <script>const ASSETS = {usedAssetsJSON};</script>

  <!-- Global constants -->
  <script>
    const PALETTE = {paletteJSON};
    const DURATION = {scene.duration};
    const ROUGHNESS = {scene.roughnessLevel};
    const FONT = '{globalStyle.font}';
    const WIDTH = 1920;
    const HEIGHT = 1080;
  </script>

  <!-- Layer code: each layer runs its animation -->
  <!-- Layers respect startAt timing via setTimeout -->
  <script>
    async function runAllLayers() {
      {layers.map(layer => `
        // Layer: ${layer.label} (${layer.type})
        setTimeout(async () => {
          ${layer.generatedCode}
        }, ${layer.startAt * 1000});
      `).join('\n')}
    }
    
    // Auto-calc stroke lengths for SVG layers
    document.querySelectorAll('.stroke').forEach(el => {
      if (el.getTotalLength) {
        el.style.setProperty('--len', el.getTotalLength());
      }
    });
    
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', runAllLayers);
  </script>

  <!-- Audio -->
  {audioHTML}

</body>
</html>
```

### 6.2 Layer HTML rendering

```ts
function renderLayer(layer: SceneLayer): string {
  const baseStyle = `
    opacity: ${layer.opacity};
    mix-blend-mode: ${layer.blendMode};
    z-index: ${layer.zIndex};
  `;

  switch (layer.type) {
    case 'canvas2d':
      return `<canvas id="${layer.id}" class="inkframe-layer"
                width="1920" height="1080"
                style="${baseStyle}"></canvas>`;

    case 'svg':
      return `<svg id="${layer.id}" class="inkframe-layer"
                viewBox="0 0 1920 1080"
                style="${baseStyle}">
                ${layer.generatedCode}
              </svg>`;
              // Note: for SVG layers, generatedCode is SVG markup
              // not JS. The stroke-dashoffset CSS animations run
              // automatically.

    case 'd3':
      return `<div id="${layer.id}" class="inkframe-layer"
                style="${baseStyle}">
              </div>`;
              // D3 code appends SVG to this div

    case 'three':
      return `<div id="${layer.id}" class="inkframe-layer"
                style="${baseStyle}">
              </div>`;
              // Three.js appends canvas to this div

    case 'lottie':
      return `<div id="${layer.id}" class="inkframe-layer"
                style="${baseStyle}">
              </div>`;

    case 'html':
      return `<div id="${layer.id}" class="inkframe-layer"
                style="${baseStyle}; font-family: ${globalStyle.font}">
                ${layer.generatedCode}
              </div>`;
              // HTML layers: generatedCode is raw HTML

    case 'assets':
      return `<canvas id="${layer.id}" class="inkframe-layer"
                width="1920" height="1080"
                style="${baseStyle}"></canvas>`;
  }
}
```

