## PART 8 — IMPLEMENTATION ORDER

Build in this exact sequence. Each step is independently testable.

**Phase 1 — Foundation (Week 1)**
1. World state model (TypeScript interfaces + Zustand store)
2. SQLite persistence (world state + snapshots for undo)
3. Multi-layer scene HTML generator (static, no agent yet)
4. Preview iframe with layer compositing
5. Manual layer add/remove UI (no agent, just UI)
6. Test: manually create a scene with 3 layers, preview renders

**Phase 2 — Canvas Engine (Week 1-2)**
7. Canvas2D renderer primitives (all animateRough* functions)
8. Rough.js integration
9. Asset library (first 30 assets)
10. Asset picker UI
11. Test: draw a canvas2d scene manually

**Phase 3 — First Agent (Week 2)**
12. Scene Maker agent (single agent, no routing yet)
13. Layer code generation for canvas2d only
14. Tool: add_layer, regenerate_layer
15. Basic chat UI (no agent control panel yet)
16. SSE streaming from agent to frontend
17. Preview updates on tool completion
18. Test: "draw a diagram of how the internet works" → canvas2d scene

**Phase 4 — All Layer Types (Week 2-3)**
19. D3 layer generation + template
20. Three.js layer generation + template
21. SVG layer generation + rough.js post-processing
