## PART 9 — CRITICAL RULES (READ BEFORE WRITING CODE)

**Text rendering:**
NEVER animate text character by character anywhere in this app.
Text renders instantly via ctx.fillText() or HTML.
Timing is controlled by delay before text appears, not animation
of the text itself. This is non-negotiable.

**Determinism for WVC:**
All random values use seeded randomness (mulberry32).
Never use Math.random() in scene code.
Seeds are fixed integers, assigned by the agent per element.
This ensures WVC export matches browser preview exactly.

**Layer isolation:**
Each layer's generated code must be completely self-contained.
Layers cannot reference each other's DOM elements or variables.
Use the layer's id as a prefix for all DOM element ids within it.
Global constants (PALETTE, DURATION, ROUGHNESS, WIDTH, HEIGHT) are shared.

**Tool atomicity:**
Each tool call is a single atomic world state change.
Tools always create a snapshot before executing.
Tools always return { success, affectedSceneId, changes } so the
agent knows what happened and can inject into next decision.

**Three.js r128 constraints:**
Never use THREE.CapsuleGeometry (added in r142).
Never use ES module imports (THREE is a global).
Never use OrbitControls (not on CDN for r128).
Implement camera movement manually in the animation loop.

**D3 v7 constraints:**
d3.event was removed — use event parameter in handlers.
Always append SVG to #layerId div, never to body.
Use d3.select('#' + layerId) as the root selection.

**Rough.js seeds:**
Every animateRough* call gets a unique integer seed.
Agent increments: seed=1, seed=2, seed=3 etc per scene.
Same seed = same wobble every render. Required for WVC.

**Asset references:**
Assets are referenced by id string: ASSETS['cloud-simple'].
Never hardcode asset drawing code inline — always use drawAsset().
Asset ids are validated against the library before generation.

**Context window management:**
World state summary sent to agent: max 2000 tokens.
Full scene detail (when focused): max 3000 tokens.
Rule files: max 500 tokens each, inject max 3 at once.
Conversation history: last 10 messages only.
These limits keep costs manageable and responses fast.

**Streaming UX:**
Always stream agent text tokens to frontend.
Tool calls show "⚙ Calling {tool}..." in chat while executing.
Never block the UI waiting for tool completion.
Preview updates happen immediately after each tool, not at end.

